\title{Simple}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-16}
\taxon{definition}

\p{Let #{G} be a [[gr-000G]]. We say #{G} is \define{Simple} if the only normal subgroups of #{G} are #{\TrivialSubgroup{G}} and #{G} itself.}

\p{In other words, #{G} is simple if and only if the only proper normal subgroup of #{G} is trivial.}